text: Maboké is a food in the Central African Republic. It is a fish dish, with roasted spices, wrapped in cassava or banana leaf. It is also eaten in other parts of Africa, like the Democratic Republic of the Congo which uses many species of tropical fish from the Congo River. It is sometimes served with fried plantains and rice. ==References== Category:Central African Republic food Category:Democratic Republic of the Congo food Category:Fish dishes
title: Maboké
